==Vocabulary== ;Sum ;Difference ;Quotient ;Product
== Definitions ==
*The [[w:sum|sum]] of two unknown numbers can be written as <math>x+y</math>. *The [[w:difference|difference]] of two unknown numbers can be written as <math>x-y</math>. *The [[w:quotient|quotient]] of two unknown numbers can be written as <math>x \div y</math>. *The [[w:product (mathematics)|product]] of two unknown numbers can be written as <math>x \times y</math>.
Keep in mind that <math>x+y</math> '''is the same''' as <math>y+x</math> and <math>x \times y</math> '''is the same''' as <math>y \times x</math>.
However, <math>x-y</math> '''is not the same''' as <math>y-x</math>, and <math>x \div y</math> '''is not the same''' as <math>y \div x</math>.
