<!-- EDIT TEMPLATE DOCUMENTATION BELOW THIS LINE -->
This template will allow you to create a local or [[Help:Editing#Interwiki links|interwiki link]] (such as a link to the [[Help:Tracking changes#Page history|history of a page]]) on a page without having the [[File:External.svg|10px|link=]] follow the link. This can be used, for example, when internal or interwiki links appear as external links. 

===Examples===

*<code><nowiki>{{plain link|url=http://www.wikibooks.org}}</nowiki></code> gives {{Plain link|url=http://www.wikibooks.org}}
*<code><nowiki>{{plain link|http://www.wikibooks.org Wikibooks}}</nowiki></code> gives {{Plain link|http://www.wikibooks.org Wikibooks}}
*<code><nowiki>{{plain link|http://www.wikibooks.org | Wikibooks}}</nowiki></code> gives {{Plain link|http://www.wikibooks.org|Wikibooks}}

Note that if your url or link title contains an equals sign <code>=</code> you must use named parameters:
*<code><nowiki>{{plainlink | url=http://en.wikibooks.org/w/index.php?title=Equals_sign&oldid=282228764 | name="=" }}</nowiki></code> gives {{plain link|url=http://en.wikibooks.org/w/index.php?title=Equals_sign&oldid=282228764|name="="}}
