=Theorem= Let ''f'' be a homomorphism from group <font color = Blue>G</font> to Group <font color = Green>K</font>.
Let <font color = Blue>''g''</font> be any element of <font color = Blue>G</font>.
: ''f''(<font color = FireBrick>''g''<sup>-1</sup></font>) = <font color = FireBrick>[</font>''f''(<font color = Blue>''g''</font>)<font color = FireBrick>]<sup>-1</sup></font>
=Proof= :{| Style = "width:75%;boarder:1px" |- | 0. &nbsp; <math> f({\color{Blue}g}) \circledast f({\color{BrickRed}g^{-1}}) = f({\color{Blue}g} \ast {\color{BrickRed}g^{-1}})</math> || ''f'' is a [[../Definition of Homomorphism, Kernel, and Image|homomorphism]] |- | 1. &nbsp; <math> f({\color{Blue}g}) \circledast f({\color{BrickRed}g^{-1}}) = f({\color{Blue}e_{G}})</math> || definition of [[../../Group/Definition of a Group/Definition of Inverse|inverse]] in G |- | . || |- | 2. &nbsp; <math> f({\color{Blue}g}) \circledast f({\color{BrickRed}g^{-1}}) = {\color{OliveGreen}e_{K}}</math> || homomorphism ''f'' [[../Homomorphism Maps Identity to Identity|maps identity to identity]] |- | 3. &nbsp; <math> {\color{BrickRed} [} f({\color{Blue}g}) {\color{BrickRed}]^{-1}} \circledast f({\color{Blue}g}) \circledast f({\color{BrickRed}g^{-1}}) = {\color{BrickRed} [} f({\color{Blue}g}) {\color{BrickRed}]^{-1}} \circledast {\color{OliveGreen}e_{K}}</math> || as f(<font color = blue>g</font>) is in K, so is its [[../../Group/Definition of a Group/Definition of Inverse|inverse]] <font color = FireBrick>[</font>''f''(<font color = Blue>''g''</font>)<font color = FireBrick>]<sup>-1</sup></font> |- | . || |- | 4. &nbsp; <math> {\color{OliveGreen}e_{K}} \circledast f({\color{BrickRed}g^{-1}}) = {\color{BrickRed} [} f({\color{Blue}g}) {\color{BrickRed}]^{-1}} </math> || [[../../Group/Definition of a Group/Definition of Inverse|inverse]] on K, <font color = green>''e''<sub>K</sub></font> is [[../../Group/Definition of a Group/Definition of Identity|identity]] of K |- | 5. &nbsp; <math> f({\color{BrickRed}g^{-1}}) = {\color{BrickRed} [} f({\color{Blue}g}) {\color{BrickRed}]^{-1}} </math> || <font color = green>''e''<sub>K</sub></font> is [[../../Group/Definition of a Group/Definition of Identity|identity]] of K |}
