I think the ''if'' definition should say

<nowiki>if (boolean expression) {
    statement
}</nowiki> 

with "statement" instead of "expression"

I'm just learning perl, so I don't dare to make the change myself. However, AFAIK, the if statement doesn't return the values of the statements/expressions executed.

