''8 points can be earned with this task.  Every wrong sentence reduces the score by 1.

== Task 2: About the planets ==

{{question-answer|question=Is Mercury hot everywhere?|answer=No (it's cold in the shadow).}}
{{question-answer|question=Why does Venus appear to us to shine like a star?|answer=There are clouds hanging above Venus which reflect the sunlight.}}
{{question-answer|question=How many kilometres from the Sun is Earth?|answer=About 150 million.}}
{{question-answer|question=Why is it so cold on Mars?|answer=It's so far from the sun.}}
{{question-answer|question=What is the Great Red Spot on Jupiter?|answer=A storm.}}
{{question-answer|question=What are the rings of Saturn like?|answer=Sand, rocks, and ice.}}
{{question-answer|question=Is Uranus the only planet standing straight up?|answer=No (actually it's on its side).}}
{{question-answer|question=Is there water on Neptune?|answer=No (Neptune is named after the Roman god of the seas, but there is no water on Neptune).}}

''8 points can be earned with this task. Every right answer gives 1 point.''

